Tập xác định $\mathscr{D}=[-1;1].$
\begin{align*}
y'&=0 \\
\Leftrightarrow \sqrt{1-x^2}-x\cdot\dfrac{x}{\sqrt{1-x^2}}&=0\\
\Rightarrow 1-2x^2 &= 0 \\
\Leftrightarrow x&=\pm \dfrac{1}{\sqrt{2}}
\end{align*}
Có $y(\pm 1)=0$, $y\left(\dfrac{1}{\sqrt{2}}\right)=\dfrac{1}{2}$, $y\left(-\dfrac{1}{\sqrt{2}}\right)=-\dfrac{1}{2}$.
Vậy $\min y=-\dfrac{1}{2}\cdot$
